// ============================================================================
// Purpose:
//   VContainer composition root that wires all Models, Systems, Views, and
//   MessagePipe brokers for a scope (scene, feature, or app-wide).
//
// Placeholders to replace:
//   {{NAMESPACE}}   — Full namespace (e.g., MyGame.Core)
//   {{CLASS_NAME}}  — PascalCase class name (e.g., GameLifetimeScope)
//   {{DESCRIPTION}} — One-line summary of what this scope covers
//
// Conventions enforced:
//   - Models registered as Singleton (shared state within scope)
//   - Systems registered as Singleton with AsImplementedInterfaces().AsSelf()
//   - Views registered via RegisterComponentInHierarchy (scene binding)
//   - MessagePipe brokers registered per message type
//   - sealed class by default
//
// Scope hierarchy:
//   RootLifetimeScope        — app-wide (audio, save, settings)
//     └─ SceneLifetimeScope  — per-scene (gameplay systems and models)
//          └─ Child scopes   — per-feature (UI popups, spawned entities)
// ============================================================================

